node.text:
For the love of pizza! Make authentic Neapolitan pizza in your backyard. 

For years, pizza pros have said you just can’t make Neapolitan pizza at home. But the game has changed. The new Ooni Karu 16 Multi-Fuel Pizza Oven is the first and only pizza oven to be ‘Recommended for Domestic Use’ by the Associazione Verace Pizza Napoletana (AVPN), the acclaimed international authority on Neapolitan pizza.

That’s a BIG deal! 

The @pizzanapoletanaverace has two purposes: to preserve the authorship of Neapolitan pizza and to teach the world how to achieve true Neapolitan pizza. 

We submitted ourselves to their scrutinizing standards, and we are so pleased with the result. Here’s Antonio Pace, Founder & President of the AVPN, explaining why they recommend Ooni Karu 16! Helping to uphold Neapolitan tradition is a great honor and achievement.

node.title: Ooni x AVPN | Ooni Karu 16 Recommended for Domestic Use

New York-based sourdough enthusiast and Ooni Ambassador Christy Alia of @realcleverfood shows off just how easy it is to set up and get the Ooni Karu 16 primed for action. Now she’s ready to make Sicilian scacciata, calzones, and lots of beautiful leopard-spotted pizza in taking advantage of Karu 16’s improved insulation and improved airflow. 

Want the full Karu 16 rundown? Find a complete list of its product features here: https://bit.ly/3pQmGUY

node.text:
We are proud to introduce one of our newest Ooni Ambassadors, Francesco Albanese (@kneadingwithfranco).

Franco is a London-based home pizzaiolo with a passion for Neapolitan pizza. He shares his creations in hopes of inspiring others and helping them attain that perfect pizza and or perfectly kneaded dough.

One of his latest creations, cooked in the Ooni Koda 16, is topped with ripe pear, Stilton cheese, and walnuts. He finishes it with a drizzle of honey and some fresh basil post-bake, and, well, let’s just say we can’t wait to make this combo for ourselves.

With multiple fuel options, try using wood and/or charcoal for the joy of the pizza purist experience and a subtle wood-fired flavor, or go for a low-maintenance cooking experience with an Ooni Gas Burner – sold separately. 

Fresh flame-cooked pizza is achievable in just 60 seconds in the comfort of your backyard. What's not to love? Pre-order today!

node.text:
It's the #RandomPizzaToppingChallenge: International Hawaiian Pizza Day Edition! 🍍

Ah, the age-old debate: Does pineapple belong on a pizza? The answer has wrought havoc at dinner tables and pitted family and friends against one another.

Brussel Sprouts? Anchovies? Marmite? These foods have all provoked disagreements but nothing has generated the same furious debate across the globe as Hawaiian pizza. 

Here are a fine line-up of pineapple pizzas, and to us, they look delicious?! Maybe delicious enough to turn a pineapple-hater's head. From the caramelized pineapple from @realcleverfood or the pineapple-saffron glazed gammon from @planetfriendlyfirewood - we are convinced! Why not join in on this bonus round and share your pineapple pizzas with us and be sure to tag #RandomPizzaToppingChallenge. 

Many thanks to @scottspizzaproject, @realcleverfood, @northernfoodlad, @allaneats, and @planetfriendlyfirewood. We know putting pineapple on a pizza must've been hard for some of you. 😉

Ooni users have told us that one of the things they love most about cooking with their oven is the ability to connect with folks over the making and sharing of great pizza, so a few years ago, we created a global cookout event to do just that. Mark your calendars, because this year, Ooni Day will take place on September 18th!

With Ooni Day right around the corner, we thought we'd share our Quick Pizza Dough recipe, a same-day dough that takes under an hour to make, from mixing to baking.

All you need is a warm place where the dough can rest, and some dusting flour to prevent it from sticking. Get the full recipe at the link in bio. 🔥

node.text:
Ahhh, the joy of pizza. Just mentioning the word can bring a smile to your face (or at least it does for @thezareport here). 

Maybe it’s the way the cheese pulls as you take your first bite. Or the way the flavors dance across every taste bud, celebrating the contrasting textures of gooey, melted cheese and crispy crust. 

Or maybe it’s not the pizza itself, but the way it makes us feel. Giddy. Gleeful. Content. However you choose to characterize it, pizza is there to pick us up.  Check out how we’re celebrating the #JoyOfPizza at the link in bio.

📸: Valerie Rizzo

node.text:
Kevin Liebl (@lieblingsessen_) is a kindergarten teacher and a passionate cook. When the devastating floods hit Germany in July, he rolled up his sleeves and raised money to help reopen a flooded kindergarten in Salmtal, Germany. He also bought water and pizza ingredients, then set about baking pizzas for flood relief volunteers using his Ooni Fyra 12. 

A small act of kindness can go a long way. Do you know anyone doing extraordinary things to help others? Enter them into our Slice of Kindness competition, and they’ll have a  chance to win a complete Ooni setup to aid their future efforts. Nominations close next Monday (August 23rd). Link in bio.

Well American Ooni fans, we have some capital ‘N’ NEWS: From now until midnight on August 30th, we’re running sweepstakes to give away a prize pack from @muttipomodorousa, @kingarthurbaking, @thetablelesstraveled, and of course, Ooni.

node.text:
Our Spain-based Ooni Ambassador, @luigi.di.domenico, always produces the goods using his Ooni Koda 16.

Luigi tells us what the #JoyOfPizza means to him! He loves to teach the art of great pizza, but the real joy comes when he sees the happiness that is created as a result of his tips and recipes. The joy of pizza can mean many things, but one thing’s for sure, pizza can connect us all.

node.text:
Our Content Production Coordinator, Edith, was taking her daily lunchtime stroll in Glasgow when she stumbled across a pizza stand powered by an Ooni Pro 16. It was run by Glasgow children's charity PEEK, who were busy firing out pizzas for local kids and their families. PEEK works to create enhancement opportunities for children across Scotland through interactive sessions and events — which in this case, meant classes on using the oven and cooking pizzas. Hooray for pizza education! 

Do you know an individual, group, or organization spreading slices of joy in your area? If so, nominate them as part of our Slice of Kindness competition, and they could win a complete Ooni setup! Nominations close on August 23rd, so head to the link in bio and get your submission in while you can.
